OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F435A1718848656
OL,3,CStruggling recruit escaped base while
OL,4,CCCTV camera 'pointed at the ground'
OL,6,FHe had managed to escape the base
OL,7,Funnoticed because the nearest security
OL,8,Fcamera was pointing at the ground for
OL,9,Fan hour and a half.
OL,11,FMajor Mark Latham told the inquest in
OL,12,FExeter, a review of CCTV footage that
OL,13,Ftook place after the tragedy showed an
OL,14,Foperator was in control of a camera at
OL,15,Fthe corner of the base until 2.20am.
OL,16,FThe same camera next moved at 3.50am.
OL,18,FHe said that weeks later, he had seen
OL,19,Fa still image of the footage and at
OL,20,Fthat point noticed there was a duvet
OL,21,Fagainst the fence.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/16
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
